1.title: Islands of the Bahamas
1.plot: The Bahamas have grown into Private Island real estate's most in-demand market. Escape to the most exotic and remote islands a multi-millionaire buyer, celebrity, or luxury-seeking tourist can find.

2.title: Musha Cay and the Islands of Copperfield Bay
2.plot: Join us as we explore the most magical and luxurious private resort island in the world. Owned by famed illusionist David Copperfield, who purchased the island at a cost of $50 million, Musha Cay, provides a memorable one-of-a-kind experience like nowhere else on Earth.

3.title: Desroches
3.plot: We're traveling 1,000 miles away from anywhere in search of the perfect private island. Forget about the jet lag because when you land in paradise, your dream becomes reality. It's first-class service on the private island of Desroches.

4.title: Emerald Cay
4.plot: There's nothing like it in the Caribbean, or even in the world! The result of seven years of construction, Emerald Cay in Turks and Caicos combines pristine natural beauty with state-of-the-art luxury to provide the ultimate private island paradise.

5.title: Turks and Caicos
5.plot: Come see how the affluent are rediscovering themselves in the private island of Turks and Caicos. Immerse yourself in sunshine, sea and surf, just 500 miles off the coast of Florida. Life's short, but your quality time doesn't have to be!

6.title: French Polynesia
6.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich as she takes you on a magical journey through the private island of French Polynesia. Discover heaven on earth in your own utopian paradise full of beauty, adventure and above all, sheer escapism.

7.title: Peter Island
7.plot: Tales of pirates, betrayal and hidden treasure all share a part of this island's past. There are some places on earth that simply must be experienced to fully understand and Peter Island in the British Virgin Islands is one of those places.

8.title: Roatan
8.plot: Roatan is one of the best kept secrets of the Caribbean. We take viewers on an underwater adventure and show the most luxurious private islands Honduras has to offer.

9.title: Florida Keys
9.plot: From Miami to colorful Key West, the Florida Keys have become one of the America's favorite tropical escapes. Join host Christina Cindrich as she takes you to some of the most secluded private islands for an experience that cannot be beat.

10.title: Belize
10.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich in a country that combines both adventure and luxury into one complete island experience. With one foot planted in the mysterious jungles and the other dipped in the Caribbean Sea, Belize will awaken all of your senses.

11.title: Calivigny Island
11.plot: Located off the coast of "The Spice Isle" Granada in the Caribbean is one of the most luxurious private islands you'll ever see. Calivigny Island is truly the ultimate escape for the affluent traveler in search of their own slice of paradise.

1.title: Little Bokeelia
1.plot: You'll live as few have lived before in a place where the finest luxuries co-exist in absolute harmony with nature. This is Little Bokeelia Island, a private island paradise that could be yours.

2.title: Fiji: Paradise in the Pacific
2.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich as she takes you to one of the world's most exotic destinations, Fiji! Noted for its magical landscape, stunning beaches, and friendly people, these islands are a spectacular taste of heaven right here on Earth.

3.title: Fiji: Exotic Escape
3.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich in the postcard perfect island nation of Fiji. With its white sandy beaches, fascinating culture and magical underwater world, this is an unforgettable Private Island experience that you'll never want to be rescued from!

4.title: Jumby Bay
4.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich on a 300-acre private island paradise off the coast of Antigua. With its gorgeous villas and multi-million dollar estates, Jumby Bay's beauty will cast an unforgettable spell of serene enchantment.

5.title: Four Seasons Maldives
5.plot: Join host Christina Cindrich for an unforgettable experience on two Four Seasons luxury island resorts in the Maldives. Your postcard perfect paradise will come to life right before your eyes in a destination that will surely take your breath away.

6.title: Christina's Top 10
6.plot: Experience the romance of the South Pacific, the laid-back beauty of the Caribbean, the adventure of Central America and the exotic splendor of Asia. Host Christina Cindrich takes you to her top 10 most incredible private islands in the world.

7.title: Phuket, Thailand
7.plot: Perhaps nowhere else in Thailand can you enjoy the combination of sun, beach and nightlife quite like in Phuket. Thailand's largest and most popular island seduces its visitors with a vibrant mix of nighttime entertainment and beach culture.

8.title: Isla Simca
8.plot: Isla Simca is a jungle hideaway where natural beauty, art, adventure and architecture fuse into a one-of-a-kind retreat. Join host Christina Cindrich on this Panamanian island that until now has been hidden away from the world's prying eyes!

9.title: The Grenadines
9.plot: The Grenadines, an island chain deep in the Caribbean. The name alone elicit visions of exotic and peaceful scenery. St. Vincent being the largest, but away from the hustle and traffic, become mesmerized by the beauty of these castaway islands.

10.title: Laucala
10.plot: The name Laucala is whispered in all the best circles - partly because only the best know how to pronounce it. Owned by the co-founder of Red Bull, this Fijan paradise is one of the world's top island resorts and once there it's easy to see why.

11.title: Bora Bora
11.plot: If you believe in love at first sight, then Bora Bora is where you'll find it. Nestled in the South Pacific at the heart of French Polynesia, Bora Bora is, simply put, everything it's supposed to be. One of the few places on Earth that everyone hopes to witness in their lifetime - and once you see it, you are forever captivated.

12.title: Zambia
12.plot: In the heart of the African subcontinent lies a destination known as the "real Africa". This is Zambia. Blessed with awe-inspiring natural wonders and an abundance of wildlife, Zambia retains its essence: the authentic feeling of a wilderness which is wild, beautiful, and slightly unpredictable.

1.title: Philippines
1.plot: In the middle of the South Pacific Ocean...along the Ring of Fire...is the second-largest island archipelago in the world. With over 7,000 individual islands and a spread of screensaver-perfect backdrops - from dreamy tropical beaches and smoldering volcanoes, to a busting metropolis - the Philippines is one of south-east Asia's most exotic getaways. A diverse country in a small package...where you can have a piece of paradise all to yourself. If you're ready to explore - you're in for a truly rewarding experience.

2.title: Palau
2.plot: Located within the larger region of Micronesia, Palau is southeast of the Philippines and 400 miles north of the equator. An island nation made up of more than 500 islands, including the mind-blowing, mushroom-like Rock Islands, situated at the bio-diverse intersection of the Pacific Ocean and Philippine Sea. Time stopped when these gorgeous islands took shape at the end of the last ice age...gifting us with one of the most geologically and biologically fascinating places on the planet.

3.title: Scrub Island
3.plot: It's a place where waters bloom together in every shade of blue. The soft Caribbean breezes sweep around your skin, and you're going to get sand between your toes, eventually. Join host Tabitha Lipkin as she explores Scrub Island, which is part of the British Virgin Islands. A private island designed with every imaginable luxury in mind, and once you come, you may never leave.

4.title: Laamu
4.plot: Laamu. When you hear that name, what exactly do you think of? It's a foreign, yet exotic word for shore, but what could it possibly mean, and where does the name come from? If the sound of the word "Laamu" instantly transports you deep into the Indian Ocean where the vibrancy of corals mix perfectly with the granary of the Inner Islands, then you're off to a good start. 500 miles south of the tip of India, it's a land where volcanoes once were king, ripping through crystal clear waters to slowly build up the islands of the Maldives. 5.title: St. Lucia
5.plot: St. Lucia. There's simply no place in the world that can and will take your breath away like the sight of St. Lucia. There are islands, and then, there are islands. St. Lucia is an island nation situated just below the Virgin Islands, but above St. Vincent and the Grenadines. Here you'll find everything an exotic getaway has to offer. Plus, you'll get lost in the culture and paradise that you didn't even realize was a part of our world.
